00:13:53,807 --> 00:13:55,548
where your eye tends to focus anyway.

261
00:13:56,100 --> 00:14:09,169
The core principles of value and saturation and all that and palette is still really good around the scene, but there's nowhere near as much detail, which you might not even notice at first, as soon as you get away from the face the detail just drops

262
00:14:09,169 --> 00:14:20,057
away, because the artist wants you to focus here. And what we found is if you actually put detail everywhere. It confuses the player, then are the keys of the viewer then they don't know where to look.

263
00:14:20,620 --> 00:14:24,024
So composition and attention to detail really matters,

264
00:14:24,024 --> 00:14:26,887
and especially not putting the detail everywhere

265
00:14:26,887 --> 00:14:28,509
in the painting is really critical,

266
00:14:28,509 --> 00:14:31,352
and for us especially, because we're also limited in time

